25|$|As of 2004, 5 {{mutations}} {{have been}} found to enhance insulin secretion. Heterozygosity for gain of function mutations reduces the threshold glucose that triggers insulin release. This creates hypoglycemia of varying patterns, including transient or persistent congenital <b>hyperinsulinism,</b> or fasting or reactive hypoglycemia appearing at an older age.|$|E
