50|$|Clinical {{features}} and circumstances can provide other indirect evidence of <b>hyperinsulinism.</b> For instance, babies with neonatal <b>hyperinsulinism</b> are often large for gestational age {{and may have}} other features such as enlarged heart and liver. Knowing that someone takes insulin or oral hypoglycemic agents for diabetes obviously makes insulin excess the presumptive cause of any hypoglycemia.|$|E
