50|$|Hypoglycemia {{was first}} {{recognized}} in the 19th century. In the 1920s, after the discovery of insulin and its use {{in the treatment of}} diabetics, <b>hyperinsulinism</b> was suspected to be a cause of hypoglycemia in non-diabetics. A pioneering description of <b>hyperinsulinism</b> as a cause of hypoglycemia was published by Seale Harris in 1924. The first report of a surgical cure of hypoglycemia by removing an islet cell tumour was in 1929.|$|E
