50|$|The SUR1 {{protein is}} coded by the ABCC8 gene and is {{associated}} with congenital <b>hyperinsulinism</b> and susceptibility to type 2 diabetes.|$|E
50|$|<b>Hyperinsulinism</b> {{may also}} refer to forms of {{hypoglycemia}} caused by excessive insulin secretion. In normal children and adults, insulin secretion should be minimal when blood glucose levels fall below 70 mg/dL (3.9 mM). There are {{many forms of}} hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia caused by various types of insulin excess. Some of those that occur in infants and young children are termed congenital <b>hyperinsulinism.</b> In adults, severe hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia is often due to an insulinoma, an insulin-secreting tumor of the pancreas.|$|E
